defs.docs:
nphysics
========
**nphysics** is a 2 and 3-dimensional physics engine for games and animations.
It uses [ncollide](http://ncollide.org) for collision detection, and
[nalgebra](http://nalgebra.org) for vector/matrix math. 2D and 3D
implementations both share the same code!

defs.name: RigidBodyCollisionGroups
defs.docs:
Groups of collision used to filter which object collide with which other one.
 nphysics use a specific group for its own purposes (i.e. the group of static objects).
 The `group 29` is reserved and you cannot use it.

 The `group 29` is reserved and you cannot use it.
